@startuml t_component_04_notes_skinparam
title Component Diagram — Notes, Skinparam & Visual Directives\n(all note forms, skinparam block+inline, hide/remove/restore, tags)

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 1. SKINPARAM — BLOCK FORM per element type
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor #E8F4FD
    BorderColor #1565C0
    FontSize 12
    FontStyle bold
    RoundCorner 8
    BorderThickness 1.5
    shadowing false
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #E8F5E9
    BorderColor #2E7D32
    FontSize 11
}

skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #FFF9C4
    BorderColor #F9A825
    FontSize 13
    RoundCorner 6
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    BorderColor #F57F17
    FontSize 10
    FontColor #4E342E
}

skinparam arrow {
    Color #444444
    FontSize 10
    Thickness 1.2
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 2. SKINPARAM — INLINE / STEREOTYPE-SPECIFIC FORM
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

skinparam component<<service>> {
    BackgroundColor #FCE4EC
    BorderColor #C62828
}
skinparam component<<repository>> {
    BackgroundColor #E8F5E9
    BorderColor #1B5E20
}
skinparam component<<gateway>> {
    BackgroundColor #EDE7F6
    BorderColor #4527A0
}
skinparam component<<external>> {
    BackgroundColor #ECEFF1
    BorderColor #546E7A
    FontStyle italic
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 3. COMPONENTS for note attachment targets
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[ComponentA] as CA
[ComponentB] as CB <<service>>
[ComponentC] as CC <<repository>>
[ComponentD] as CD <<gateway>>
[ComponentE] as CE <<external>>
[ComponentF] as CF
[ComponentG] as CG

() "InterfaceA" as IA
() "InterfaceB" as IB
interface InterfaceC as IC

package "System Core" as CORE #EEF2FF {
    [CoreService] as CS <<service>>
    [CoreRepo] as CR <<repository>>
    [CoreGateway] as CGW <<gateway>>
}

package "External Layer" as EXT_LAYER #ECEFF1 {
    [ExtService1] as ES1 <<external>>
    [ExtService2] as ES2 <<external>>
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 4. NOTE FORMS — all positional variants
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' Single-line positional notes
note top of CA : Single line top note
note bottom of CB : Single line bottom note
note left of CC : Single line left note
note right of CD : Single line right note

' Multi-line positional notes
note top of CE
    Multi-line top note
    with two lines
end note

note bottom of CF
    Multi-line bottom note
    line one
    line two
    line three
end note

note left of CG
    Multi-line left note
    with content
end note

note right of CORE
    **Multi-line right of package**
    This note attaches to
    the package container itself.
    Parser must handle: note right of ALIAS
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 5. FLOATING NOTES  (note as N ... end note)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note as FLOAT_1
    Floating note — no attachment.
    Declared with: note as ALIAS
    Can be linked via .. to components.
end note

note as FLOAT_2 #FFE0B2
    Colored floating note.
    Background color applied inline.
end note

note as FLOAT_3
    **Creole markup in note:**
    - **bold** text
    - //italic// text
    - ""monospace"" text
    - --strikethrough-- text
    - <color:red>colored</color> text
    - <back:yellow>highlighted</back>
    - <size:14>larger font</size>
    ====
    Horizontal rule above
end note

' Link floating notes to components
FLOAT_1 .. CA
FLOAT_2 .. CB
FLOAT_3 .. CORE

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 6. NOTE ON LINK
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CA --> CB : first link
note on link
    Note on the CA-->CB link.
    Attaches to the most recently
    declared arrow above.
end note

CB ..> CC : second link
note on link #E8F5E9
    Colored note on link.
    Color applied to note background.
end note

CC --> CD
note on link : Single line note on link

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 7. TAG SYSTEM — $tag declarations + hide/remove/restore
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

component "Tagged Alpha" as TA $alpha $shared
component "Tagged Beta"  as TB $beta  $shared
component "Tagged Gamma" as TG $gamma
component "Untagged"     as TU

TA --> TB : alpha-to-beta
TB --> TG : beta-to-gamma
TG --> TU : gamma-to-untagged

' Tag-based visibility directives (grammar productions to parse):
' hide $alpha       -- hides all $alpha tagged elements
' remove $beta      -- removes all $beta tagged elements
' restore $shared   -- restores all $shared tagged elements
' hide @unlinked    -- hides all unlinked elements
' remove @unlinked  -- removes unlinked elements
' remove *          -- removes all elements (then restore selectively)
'
' NOTE: We declare but don't activate hide/remove here so the diagram
' renders fully — the grammar must parse these as valid directives.
' Uncomment to test rendering suppression:
' hide $alpha
' remove $beta
' restore $shared
' hide @unlinked

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 8. DIRECTION DIRECTIVE
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' left to right direction
' (commented out — activating changes layout globally;
'  grammar must parse it as a valid top-level directive)

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 9. SYSTEM LINKS
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CS --> CR : JDBC
CS --> CGW : REST
CGW ..> ES1 : HTTP
CGW ..> ES2 : HTTPS
CS -- IA : provides
IB --( CS : requires
IC -- CR

ES1 --> IA
IA --( CB

note right of EXT_LAYER
    **skinparam<<stereotype>> tested:**
    <<external>> components get
    italic gray styling via
    skinparam component<<external>>
    block form.
end note

note bottom of TA
    **Tag directive grammar:**
    hide $tagName
    remove $tagName
    restore $tagName
    hide @unlinked
    remove @unlinked
    remove *
    These are top-level statements
    parsed before rendering.
end note

@enduml
